## Resource Management

**Codex Model Limits (GPT-5.1/GPT-5-codex - November 2025):**
- Maximum concurrent: 10 instances per orchestrator
- Typical usage: 5-7 for simple code generation tasks
- Resource overhead: ~500MB RAM per instance
- Processing time: Variable (GPT-5.1: fast for reasoning workloads, GPT-5-codex: ultra-fast for code generation)

- **Performance Characteristics:**
- Simple algorithm implementation: Fast (GPT-5-codex)
- CRUD code generation: Fast (GPT-5.1/GPT-5-codex)
- Utility functions: Very fast (GPT-5-codex)
- Rapid prototyping: Fast (GPT-5.1/GPT-5-codex default)
- GPT-5-codex more cost-effective than Sonnet for pure coding workloads
- 10 parallel Codex: ~10x faster than sequential

**Cost Considerations (⭐ PREFERRED for Simple Tasks):**
- GPT-5.1/GPT-5-codex more cost-effective than Sonnet
- ⭐ PREFERRED for ALL simple code generation tasks
- Use for CRUD operations, utilities, boilerplate
- Reserve Sonnet for complex strategic reasoning only

