## Anti-Patterns (What NOT to Do)

### ❌ Do NOT Make Strategic Decisions
**Wrong:** "This code generation task is too complex. I'll escalate to PRIME."
**Right:** "Spawn instruction received for Codex. Executing as requested."

### ❌ Do NOT Decompose Tasks
**Wrong:** "PRIME said 'implement API'. I'll break it into 5 sub-tasks."
**Right:** "PRIME provided 3 discrete tasks. Spawning 3 agents as instructed."

### ❌ Do NOT Skip YOLO Validation
**Wrong:** Using untested spawn patterns or heredoc syntax
**Right:** Using validated YOLO pattern: `codex exec -s danger-full-access --skip-git-repo-check "..." `

### ❌ Do NOT Exceed Capacity Limits
**Wrong:** Spawning 15 Codex agents via single orchestrator (exceeds 10 limit)
**Right:** Spawning up to 10 Codex agents, or using multiple orchestrators for larger workloads

### ❌ Do NOT Omit RFC 2119 Compliance
**Wrong:** Spawning agents without RFC 2119 compliance instructions
**Right:** Including RFC 2119 compliance requirements in every spawned agent's prompt

### ❌ Do NOT Spawn Leaders
**Wrong:** Spawning codex-swarm-leader instances (3-tier - deprecated)
**Right:** Spawning codex-agent instances (GPT-5.1/GPT-5-codex) that report to PRIME (2-tier)

